One-time VP Michael Kijana Wamalwa's son dead             Betty Njeru  09th Dec 2019 12:01:13 GMT +0300 Betty Njeru  09th Dec 2019 12:01:13 GMT +0300 Betty Njeru   Derrick Mboya (left) fourth-born son of one-time Vice President  Kijana Wamalwa, Alice Muthoni Wamalwa (centre) second born daughter and William Wamalwa (Right), his third-born son during a press briefing on their late father’s estate. [Wilberforce Okwiri/Standard]  Derrick Mboya (left) fourth-born son of one-time Vice President  Kijana Wamalwa, Alice Muthoni Wamalwa (centre) second born daughter and William Wamalwa (Right), his third-born son during a press briefing on their late father’s estate. [Wilberforce Okwiri/Standard] Derrick Mboya (left) fourth-born son of one-time Vice President  Kijana Wamalwa, Alice Muthoni Wamalwa (centre) second born daughter and William Wamalwa (Right), his third-born son during a press briefing on their late father’s estate.     Greatly saddened by the sudden death of my dear nephew Willy Big, the 3rd born son of my late brother Michael Wamalwa Kijana,the 8th Vice President of Kenya,who passed on last evening in Kitale. Post mortem will be done tomorrow to establish the cause of death. Rest in peace Papa
— Eugene L. Wamalwa (@EugeneLWamalwa) December 9, 2019 Greatly saddened by the sudden death of my dear nephew Willy Big, the 3rd born son of my late brother Michael Wamalwa Kijana,the 8th Vice President of Kenya,who passed on last evening in Kitale. Post mortem will be done tomorrow to establish the cause of death. Rest in peace Papa December 9, 2019  Daily Nation      For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. HERE.  #mc_embed_signup{background:#fff; clear:left; font:14px Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; }
